Package es.utils.mapper.impl.element

Provides a class handling the mapping of a single element of a class.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ElementMapper<IN,GETTER_OUT,SETTER_IN,OUT>
    This class contains the informations and the logic needed the execute the mapping of an single element: a Getter: a function that take a IN type object a Transformer: a function that maps the result of the getter into the correct type for the setter a Setter: a operation that assign the result of the transformer to the destination object
    Getter<T,GETTER_OUT>
    This class handle the logic of a generic getter operation.
    Setter<U,SETTER_IN>
    This class handle the logic of a generic setter operation.

Package es.utils.mapper.impl.element Description

Provides a class handling the mapping of a single element of a class.
The package contains the following class:
  • ElementMapper : contains the informations and the logic needed the execute the mapping of an single element
  • Getter : handles the way the value to map is retrieve
  • Setter : handles the way the value is assign to the result
Author:
eschoysman
